<p>

Ths strip was available on its own "<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../413/195413.xml">
alt</link>" group: alt.comics.buffalo-roam for a couple of years.</p>
<p>

The strip was moved to the Web in 1993, after the advent of the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../303/43303.xml">
NCSA Mosaic</link> browser made viewing images directly over the Web possble. It was preceded on the Web by <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../017/901017.xml">
Doctor Fun</link></it>, a daily single panel cartoon feature that was originally created for print, but moved to the Web and is the first regularly updated cartoon on the Web. See <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../176/161176.xml">
Webcomic</link>.</p>
<p>

<it>Where the Buffalo Roam</it> ran until late 1994. An archive remains online, but new material has not been added.</p>
